  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWe've identified a bug in the downloading of genesis states that is used on Holesky and Chiado (introduced in #4653).\r\n\r\nThe problem is that we use the `reqwest::blocking::Client` to download the state, [which can panic if called from an async context](https://github.com/seanmonstar/reqwest/blob/a4e8ab694c639f889a110831041fdc93d924e504/src/blocking/client.rs#L845-L859):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/2841f60686d642fcc0785c884d43e34e47a800dc/common/eth2_network_config/src/lib.rs#L17\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/2841f60686d642fcc0785c884d43e34e47a800dc/common/eth2_network_config/src/lib.rs#L378-L386\r\n\r\nWe call it from an async context via `genesis_state` here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/2841f60686d642fcc0785c884d43e34e47a800dc/beacon_node/client/src/builder.rs#L259\r\n\r\nand here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/2841f60686d642fcc0785c884d43e34e47a800dc/beacon_node/client/src/builder.rs#L279\r\n\r\nand here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/2841f60686d642fcc0785c884d43e34e47a800dc/beacon_node/client/src/builder.rs#L380\r\n\r\ni.e. in all the cases where we are starting the client for the first time: genesis sync, and checkpoint sync from state on-disk or a URL\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v4.4.1\r\n\r\n## Impact\r\n\r\n- Has so far only been observed in debug mode (not `--release`).\r\n- Only occurs on first start-up. Once the state is downloaded it is subsequently read from the DB.\r\n- Can be worked around.\r\n\r\n## Workaround\r\n\r\nInstead of `--network holesky`, use `--testnet-dir` pointed to the [custom_config_data](https://github.com/eth-clients/holesky/tree/main/custom_config_data) for Holesky.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n- Option 1: wrap the calls in `spawn_blocking` or similar.\r\n- Option 2: use the async reqwest client in `Eth2NetworkConfig` and propagate the async-ness (this might be painful).\r\n",
